snippet.textDisplay: I love crispy pork belly ramen with a chicken broth. I make the broth by throwing a couple of kilos of chicken wings in the oven till they're very well browned then boiling them for about 12 hours. Then proceeding to strain and reduce it by about 80% making it a hyper-concentrated jelly, freeze it in ice cube trays then pop a few out when making ramen. I like doing this because the other ingredients are things I usually have on hand anyway, giving me the freedom to just make a single bowl for one night, without locking myself in for a couple of days.
snippet.textOriginal: I love crispy pork belly ramen with a chicken broth. I make the broth by throwing a couple of kilos of chicken wings in the oven till they're very well browned then boiling them for about 12 hours. Then proceeding to strain and reduce it by about 80% making it a hyper-concentrated jelly, freeze it in ice cube trays then pop a few out when making ramen. I like doing this because the other ingredients are things I usually have on hand anyway, giving me the freedom to just make a single bowl for one night, without locking myself in for a couple of days.

snippet.textDisplay:
So....

Level 1: done in 30 min to a hour
Level 2: done in 3 hours
Level 3: done tomorrow.

I mean props to Yuji and his skill, and I am sure its amazing as all get out. But if you are busy you don't have 8+ hours to wait for the stock to be ready. Sounds like I'm using a quality chicken stock and Red Boat and tossing in some spices in a tea strainer or using powered spice.
snippet.textOriginal:
So.... 

Level 1: done in 30 min to a hour
Level 2: done in 3 hours
Level 3: done tomorrow.   

I mean props to Yuji and his skill, and I am sure its amazing as all get out.  But if you are busy you don't have 8+ hours to wait for the stock to be ready.   Sounds like I'm using a quality chicken stock and Red Boat and tossing in some spices in a tea strainer or using powered spice.
